<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>What is the most important phase of the SEO process?</strong></p>
<p>The audit. Without understanding your current state, strategy is guesswork. A thorough audit reveals the highest-impact opportunities and prevents wasted effort.</p>
<p><strong>How long does the SEO process take to show results?</strong></p>
<p>Initial technical fixes can show results in weeks. Content improvements typically take 2-4 months to affect rankings. Significant organic growth usually takes 6-12 months of consistent effort.</p>
<p><strong>How often should I audit my site?</strong></p>
<p>Run a full technical audit quarterly. Review content performance monthly. Monitor rankings and traffic weekly. Competitive analysis should happen quarterly.</p>
<p><strong>What is the biggest mistake in the SEO process?</strong></p>
<p>Skipping measurement. Sites that do not track results cannot optimize. Another common mistake is focusing on tactics without a strategic framework.</p>
<p><strong>Should I hire an agency or do SEO in-house?</strong></p>
<p>It depends on your resources and expertise. In-house teams offer deep product knowledge. Agencies offer breadth of experience and established processes. Many companies use a hybrid model.</p>
<p><strong>How do I prioritize SEO tasks?</strong></p>
<p>Use an effort vs. impact matrix. Quick wins (low effort, high impact) come first. High-priority projects (high effort, high impact) follow. Avoid low-impact work regardless of effort.</p>
